Pre-Game Insights: Kenya has won three games while losing only two in their last five T20Is; they are coming off a 4-wicket win against Nigeria following a 14-run defeat against the same opponent.
Speaking of Mozambique, they have lost three while winning only two games in their last five fixtures. They defeated Rwanda by 5 wickets in the previous T20I encounter.
Others: The third match of the T20 WC Sub Regional Africa Qualifier B 2024 is set to take place between Kenya (KEN) and Mozambique (MOZ). Ruaraka Sports Club Ground in Nairobi will host this clash on October 19 at 4:20 PM (IST).
No injuries have been reported so far and both sides sets to play with their full-strengthen squad.
Pitch: The pitch seems to be bowling-friendly with an average of 125 runs in the last five T20s. Spinners have dominated here as compared to the pacers in the game. Rainy conditions expected, which could impact match proceedings.
